{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-tsx","path":"/2015/09/04/kinect-game-for-live-television/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://blog.aboutme.be"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"bec2b4d1-4f9f-5424-b001-454c2e0001d1","excerpt":"That’s a first: my code being used on live tv! A couple of months ago, I was contacted by Joachim from Ketnet. They were building a new studio for their kid’s…","html":"<p>That’s a first: my code being used on live tv! A couple of months ago, I was contacted by Joachim from <a href=\"https://ketnet.be\">Ketnet</a>. They were building a new studio for their kid’s shows, and were looking for an interactive Kinect experience.</p>\n<p>I did some experiments with Kinect and Flash in the past. But as Flash is kind dying, and front-end C++/C# isn’t really my thing, I wanted to see how far I could take javascript with Kinect.</p>\n<p>I went ahead and <a href=\"https://github.com/wouterverweirder/kinect2\">built a kinect 2 nodejs extension</a> using C++ and Javascript. In combination with <a href=\"https://www.electronjs.org/\">Electron</a> and <a href=\"https://phaser.io/\">PhaserJS</a>, Koen and I were able to build a fully working, stable Kinect game.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/dd12acda117440cbde584fcd312af991/eea4a/gameplay.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 44.5945945945946%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"kinect gameplay\"\n        title=\"kinect gameplay\"\n        src=\"/static/dd12acda117440cbde584fcd312af991/1c72d/gameplay.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/dd12acda117440cbde584fcd312af991/a80bd/gameplay.jpg 148w,\n/static/dd12acda117440cbde584fcd312af991/1c91a/gameplay.jpg 295w,\n/static/dd12acda117440cbde584fcd312af991/1c72d/gameplay.jpg 590w,\n/static/dd12acda117440cbde584fcd312af991/a8a14/gameplay.jpg 885w,\n/static/dd12acda117440cbde584fcd312af991/fbd2c/gameplay.jpg 1180w,\n/static/dd12acda117440cbde584fcd312af991/eea4a/gameplay.jpg 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I must say, it was a bit stressy when it first went live on Sunday morning (prime time for kids in the weekend!), but everything ran smoothly.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/2015/09/04/kinect-game-for-live-television/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Kinect game for live television","date":"04 Sep, 2015","description":false,"tags":["kinect","javascript","electron","nodejs"],"hasCover":true,"cover":{"publicURL":"/static/2cf61cbd85af9a62c08ea4469889b2d4/preview.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='62'%20height='62'%20viewBox='0%200%2062%2062'%20preserveAspectRatio='none'%3e%3cpath%20d='M0%209c0%208%200%2010%202%2010s5-4%204-6L5%207V2l6%201c6%201%208%203%208%206l1%203%201-2V7l1%204c0%203%200%204-2%203v7l1%202c0%202%200%202%201%201%202-2%204-7%202-7-1%201-1-1-1-3%200-5%200-5%203-5%202%200%202%200%202%204l-4%2013-18-1H0v37h63V0H43A1957%201957%200%20008%200H0v9m0%2035c0%2017%200%2017%201%204V33h10l10-1c0-2-1-3-10-3-8-1-10-2-10-3-1-1-1%207-1%2018'%20fill='%23d3d3d3'%20fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":0.7493606138107417,"src":"/static/2cf61cbd85af9a62c08ea4469889b2d4/d6678/preview.jpg","srcSet":"/static/2cf61cbd85af9a62c08ea4469889b2d4/40917/preview.jpg 293w,\n/static/2cf61cbd85af9a62c08ea4469889b2d4/3c0b6